Set Up Project Structure with Spring Boot:

Use Spring Initializer to create a new project:
Dependencies: Spring Web, Spring Data JPA, H2 Database (for testing), PostgreSQL or MySQL (if you prefer for production), Lombok (to reduce boilerplate code).
Define Entities and Relationships:

Create Java classes corresponding to each table with appropriate annotations:
@Entity for each entity class.
@Id for primary keys.
@Column for other attributes.
@OneToMany(mappedBy = "artist") in Artist (since Album has the foreign key).
@ManyToOne in Album to reference Artist.
@ManyToMany with @JoinTable(name = "album_genre") in both Album and Genre, along with appropriate annotations for join columns.
Create JPA Repositories:

Define interfaces extending JpaRepository<EntityClass, PrimaryKeyType> for each entity:
ArtistRepository, AlbumRepository, GenreRepository.
For the many-to-many relationship, you might need custom methods in Album or Genre repositories to handle operations on the join table.
