Okay, I can definitely help you plan and structure this project! It’s a classic JPA/Spring Boot REST API with CRUD operations on multiple tables—a good learning exercise. Let’s break it down step by step.

Project Overview:

You need to build a REST API for managing albums, artists, and genres. The relationships are:

One-to-Many: An Artist can have many Albums (Artist ↔ Album).
Many-to-Many: An Album can belong to multiple Genres, and a Genre can be associated with multiple Albums (Album ↔ Genre via the album_genre join table).
Entities:

Artist:

artist_id (Primary Key)
name
notes
created_at, updated_at
Album:

album_id (Primary Key)
title
release_year
artist_id (Foreign Key to Artist)
created_at, updated_at
Genre:

genre_id (Primary Key)
name
description
created_at, updated_at
AlbumGenre (Join Table):

album_id (Foreign Key to Album)
genre_id (Foreign Key to Genre)
created_at, updated_at
CRUD Operations Requirements:

Artist: All 4 CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete).
Album: All 4 CRUD operations.
Genre: At least one CRUD operation (likely Create and Read would suffice here, but check project requirements again).
AlbumGenre: CRUD operations on the join table—adding and deleting rows in this table (i.e., associating/removing albums from genres).
Steps to Build:

