Next Steps:
Generate the Spring Boot starter (https://start.spring.io) with dependencies: Spring Web, Spring Data JPA, H2 (or MySQL/PostgreSQL if you prefer), Lombok, Springdoc OpenAPI UI.
Create the three entity classes exactly as shown.
Add the repositories, services, and controllers (copy the endpoint signatures).
Drop the data.sql file into src/main/resources to pre‑populate the DB.
Run the app (./mvnw spring-boot:run) and open Swagger (http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html) to verify the API surface.
Export a Postman collection from Swagger or manually build it, then commit everything to GitHub.
That’s all you need to turn the music‑collection idea into a production‑ready, interview‑showcase project.